.TH VALKEY-CHECK-RDB 1 "2024"
.SH NAME
valkey-check-rdb \- Check integrity of Valkey RDB snapshot file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B valkey-check-rdb
filename
.SH DESCRIPTION
Valkey is a high-performance open-source key-value data store.
.PP
\fBvalkey-check-rdb\fP checks the integrity of a Valkey RDB snapshot (dump) file
and reports any corruption or structural errors found.
.SH OPTIONS
.IP "filename"
Path to the RDB file to check.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The RDB file is valid.
.TP
.B 1
The RDB file is corrupt or could not be read.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBvalkey-server\fP(1), \fBvalkey-check-aof\fP(1)
.SH AUTHOR
This manual page is maintained by the package maintainer.
Valkey was originally authored by Salvatore Sanfilippo and is now maintained
by the Valkey community <https://valkey.io>.
